      <title>1850 June 24, Nashville [TN] [to] George [House] / Mary [House]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter from Mary House to her husband George House, dated June 24, 1850. She tells him of a disturbing dream she had recently, where many of her loved one's were sick, dead or missing. She writes of the family and friends that she has been visiting and corresponding with. She mentions that cholera has come to Nashville. Their daughter Sallie adds a few lines about her kittens.</abstract>
